raw_data.title: Cloud Engineer
raw_data.description: Analyze problems in collaboration with researchers and propose solutions with appropriate combination of on-premises and cloud-based technologies such as Amazon Web Sercices (AWS), Google Cloud, and Microsoft Azure . Design solutions and maintain infrastructure as a Code with technologies such as Terraform and Ansible. Use extensive knowledge of APIs to design RESTful services, and integrate them with existing data providers, using JSON or XML as needed. Set up, maintain, and monitor various services in the IT portfolio, ensuring high quality, efficiency and availability. Integrate on-premises and cloud services with products from various strategic partners to provide clients with a comprehensive package covering all their needs. Assess overall configuration and integration along with a big-picture/enterprise view. Automate and optimize technical tasks using available tools.  Actively participate in solution design sessions with leadership and present sound and creative cloud-based ideas and solutions. Plan and deploy production solutions to client-hosted or cloud-hosted infrastructure, administer users and roles on deployed solutions and train client personnel on deployed solutions.

raw_data.title: Business Analyst
raw_data.description: Assist in applying common best practices for the industry to the customer using a knowledge base to create conceptual business models and to identify relevant issues and considerations in selecting application software packages. Assess the operational and functional baseline of an organization and its organizational components, and help to define the direction and strategy for an engagement while ensuring the organizational needs are being addressed. Typical areas addressed include Human Resources, Finance, Supply, and operations. Identify information technology inadequacies and/or deficiencies that affect the functional area’s ability to support/meet organizational goals. Support the development of functional area strategies for enhanced IT. Commensurate experience and education. Key Words: Research, planning, assessment, reporting

raw_data.title: Mobile Application Developer
raw_data.description: Serve as the Designer, Developer, and Engineer on Mobile Projects. Develop Mobile applications using Objective C, Swift, Xcode, Android, and iOS Operating system. Meet with end users and technical staff to gather business and system requirements. Architect, design, develop, and engineer user interface, service tier, data tier components, infrastructure and security for Mobile Projects. Develop standards, repeatable processes, and reusable components for Mobile applications. Assists in project planning, developing timelines, composition of technical teams, and planning resources. Assists and often leads in the development and review of technical deliverables on Mobile projects. Propose comprehensive solutions based on business and technical requirements. Develop the iOS Mobile applications using UIKit, Core Data, AVFoundation, Cocoa Touch, Health Kit, Care Kit, Research Kit, SQLite, and Apple iOS SDK. Implement Mobile apps using Table views, Collection views, Delegates, Push Notifications, Storyboards, Tab bars, Navigation bars, Completion Handlers, Protocols, NSURL Session, Singleton classes, Automatic Reference Counting (ARC), Multithreading, MVC/MVVM design patterns, REST API's, and JSON Serialization. Work with tools like Jira for project management and bugs tracking, and GitHub for Version control and Agile/Scrum Methodology. Design database architecture, create the relationship between the tables using RDBMS, and develop the SQL database tables, views, stored procedures using SQL queries. Test the Mobile apps  using Appium and XCTest to confirm that the they meet the initial functional specifications. Release the iOS applications in App Store, support and maintain the mobile applications in production.

raw_data.description: Responsible for and leads team on large complex projects. Translates customer requirements into formal agreements and plans to culminate in customer acceptance or results.
